This file defines the binary format used by ptrscan to store pointer chains.

-- extension: 

    <file>.pscan

    where <file> is a user supplied string.


 -- overview:

    <static region definitions><offsets>


 -- static region definitions

    <name_0><NULL><name_1><NULL>[...]<name_n><NULL><NULL>

    where:
      <name_x> is a string representing the 'pathname' field of proc maps.
      <name_x> is only the name, not the full path. e.g.:

        "/usr/lib/libc.so.6" in proc maps becomes "libc.so.6"

      <NULL> is a single null byte.


 -- offsets

    <offset_set_0><offset_set_1>[...]<offset_set_n>

    where:
      <offset_set_x> is a set of offsets starting with the static offset.


 -- offset set

    <static_region_id><offset_0><offset_1>[...]<offset_n><UINT32_MAX>

    where:
      <static_region_id> is an index into static region definitions.
      <offset_x> is a single uint32_t offset.
      
      <UINT32_MAX> is the max value uint32_t can hold: 0xFFFFFFFF
